  "title": "Compare potential difference",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a circuit that contains a battery, two resistors, a capacitor, and a switch. The left side contains a battery labeled script E. Moving up the left side and across the top, is a resistor labeled R 1. To the right of the resistor labeled R 1, the circuit splits into two vertical branches. The first vertical branch has a capacitor labeled C. Moving down the second vertical branch is a switch labeled S, and a resistor labeled R 2.\" height=\"216\" src=\"/images/3ef8eece7920facde2ecf3c6f8d9a3bf.png\" width=\"450\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two identical resistors, an uncharged capacitor, and a switch are connected to a battery in the circuit shown above. The switch is open and the circuit is allowed to reach steady state. The switch is then closed and the circuit again reaches steady state. Which of the following correctly compares the potential difference across resistor <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R 1\"><math alttext=\"R 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> before and after the switch is closed and explains the comparison?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential across <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R 1\"><math alttext=\"R 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is less after the switch is closed because the total resistance of the circuit increases.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential across <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R 1\"><math alttext=\"R 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is less after the switch is closed because the potential difference across the battery is now split between the two resistors.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential across <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R 1\"><math alttext=\"R 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>  is greater after the switch is closed because before the switch is closed there is no current in <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R 1\"><math alttext=\"R 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and after the switch is closed there is a current.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential across <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R 1\"><math alttext=\"R 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is greater after the switch is closed because the total resistance of the circuit decreases.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
